description:
**About Jia Law Group:**

Jia Law Group is a full-service global law firm headquartered in New York City with offices in California and China. We are a growing firm seeking people that will fit in well with our firm’s culture and atmosphere. Successful candidates will have a demonstrated record of attention to details and excellent communication and writing skills.

**Position Summary:**

Reporting to the Operations Manager, the Operations Assistant will perform a wide variety of tasks. Responsibilities will include but not limited to the following:

**The Role:**

* Maintain existing vendor database and development new high-quality vendors;
* Assist the operations team with daily office management, including headquarter and branch offices;
* Manage conference room scheduling and coordination, greeting clients and guests as they arrive in a professional manner;
* Troubleshoot in-house technology issues (computers, ipads, wifi, fax, phones etc) and coordinate with external technical support to timely solve the problems;
* Order, store and organize all office supplies;
* Enter a variety of data into data trackers, including but not limited to, purchase order invoices and a record of mail received and shipped;
* Bind meeting materials, copy and print documents;
* Manage and store the firm’s file databases and physical archives in accordance with firm standards;
* Act as a liaison between the logistic and operations department;
* Comply with and understand firm operation, policies and procedures. Perform other related duties as assigned.
* Record day to day financial transactions and complete the posting process;

**Qualifications:**

* Undergraduate degree;
* Related administrative experience (preferred);
* Experience with Microsoft and Google Suite of products;
* Excellent analytical, troubleshooting, organizational, and planning skills;
* Ability to handle sensitive matters and maintain confidentiality; and
* Strong attention to detail.

**Benefits:**

We offer a robust suite of benefits including: paid time off, floating holiday, 401(k), affordable health insurance including dental & vision coverage, health savings account and flexible spending accounts to help offset the cost of dependent care and/or health care expenses, Teladoc (24/7 access to a doctor by phone or online video), One Medical membership, HealthAdvocate, online mental health therapy, commuter benefits, fitness membership, free coffee and snacks.

**Working Hours and Days:**

Monday to Friday: 9 AM to 5:30 PM

**Job Type:**

Full-time In Person

**Education:**

* Bachelor's (Preferred)

**Work authorization:**

* United States (Required)

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: $20.00 per hour

Expected hours: 40 per week

Benefits:

* 401(k)
* Dental insurance
* Health insurance
* Vision insurance

Schedule:

* Monday to Friday

Ability to Relocate:

* New York, NY 10005: Relocate before starting work (Required)

Work Location: In person
